07/08/2003
BIJELJINA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Representatives of the EU Police Mission commended the recent improvement in BiH border control while visiting the municipality of Bijeljina Wednesday (6 August).
The delegation said that police authorities at the border collected large amounts of illegally transported goods and broke criminal human trafficking networks during recent operations, demonstrating the country's progress in fighting organised crime.
Meanwhile, the border commission of Serbia-Montenegro presented a proposal to BiH for resolving open border issues.
BiH officials said the commission countries had finalised 95 per cent of the talks on the border regulations.
(RTRS, Tanjug - 06/08/03)
